 <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueanaddare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eanaddare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/1/02 12:22:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ne.jp/asahi/robin/zander/eq/chara03ett.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing in The Grey?</span><hr size=1> I'd rate the grey as &quot;heaven of necros/wiz/druid and pallies&quot;<br><br>Necro can dire charm and fear kite<br><br>Druid/Wiz can quad kite<br><br>Pally.... a bit tricky there, I found out the bottleneck of solo in the grey is mana. If you use the good old solid tanking method, I can almost grantee you will have a LONG down time.<br><br>As a very experienced pally, I'd rather use fear kite on those snakes. Yes, fear without any form of snare. Pathing around SS temple is buggy and mob will run back and forth if you fear them. All you need to do it to make sure you land every single attack (I managed to do so) and exp is crazy since almost no downtime.<br><br>I'd say high 50s can solo there, but I would suggest you to stick in KC basement in group until 60 with SU2. Slay undead proc every 2-3 mob and it indeed reduce the downtime and speed up your experience significantly.<br><br>Eana <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzosa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zosa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 151<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/2/02 5:34:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Soloing in The Grey?</span><hr size=1> Grab a friend, chanter preferred, you can kill almost everything in zone except the 55 leveled named, those ones tore me apart. With clarity, haste and slow, it is easy. If occasionally you and chanter low on mana, simply have the chanter charm one of the snake and let it kill a golem, very very easy xp, if you get a druid to come alone, wow, you can kill 3 mobs at one go, even better.<br><br>Note: druids are abundant in the zone, so that shouldn't be a problem, main issue is to come up with a chanter. I was lucky that I managed to talk one of mine friend to play chanter.<br><br>Varutia silvonesit<br>Level 55 Paladin<br>Terris Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukryssniall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kryssniall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/3/02 10:56:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing in The Grey?</span><hr size=1> Hm. One of my good friends plays a chanter, and both my sister and my girlfriend have druids. I'll have to see if I can bring them out there. <br><br>Thanks for the input! <p><img src="http://www.lvcm.com/games/pictures/kryssniallcard.jpg"><br><br><b>For the last time, those aren't pantyhose, they're breeches! <i>BREECHES!</b></i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhazielsof.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haziel SoF</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 10:18:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=4>Reply</a>